\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wpd1665702801317.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wpd1665702801317.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wpd1665702801317.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wpd1665702801317\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                       \n Checksum (CRC)\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Determines whether the <code class=\"ph codeph\">crc</code> data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. CRC checksum values are produced by Uniface when loading data from a database, or when creating or loading data from XML streams. Valid values are <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">False</code> (default).\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wpd1665702801317__section_gmd_fbf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d961651e58\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wpd1665702801317__p_d5957e1_d5958e1_d5959e1\">CRC checksum values are required for disconnected record\n        sets. They are used by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve/reconnect</span> to determine if an occurrence\n        can be updated by an XML stream. The occurrence CRC checksum can be set or inspected using\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$occcrc</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wpd1665702801317__p_d5960e1_d5961e1_d5962e1\">If <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Disconnected Record Set</span> is\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>, <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Status</span> is also set to\n        <code class=\"ph codeph\">True</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wpd1665702801317__section_rrh_gbf_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d961651e88\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"wpd1665702801317__ul_wnc_hbf_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wpd1665702801317__li_d2975e1_d2976e1_d2977e1\">DTD Entity </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qis1665702699490.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$occcrc</a><p>Set or return the CRC checksum of an occurrence.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8423894\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8423894\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Checksum (CRC) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Checksum (CRC) Determines whether the crc data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. CRC checksum values are produced by Uniface when loading data from a database, or when creating or loading data from XML streams. Valid values are True or False (default). Description CRC checksum values are required for disconnected record sets. They are used by retrieve/reconnect to determine if an occurrence can be updated by an XML stream. The occurrence CRC checksum can be set or inspected using $occcrc . If Disconnected Record Set is True , Status is also set to True . Applies To DTD Entity Related Links $occcrc Set or return the CRC checksum of an occurrence. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}